               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Miftāḥ al-jinān by Muḥammad Mujīr Mujībah Adīb</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_102-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6778">Miftāḥ al-jinān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_6778">مفتاح الجنان</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on Sufi devotions and instructions by <persName key="person_f2580" role="aut">Muḥammad Mujīr [ibn] Mujībah Adīb</persName>, the disciple of the Sufi <persName key="person_f8211" role="oth">Shaykh Nayyir al-Dīn Dihlavī</persName> (d. 757/1357). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is comprised of twenty-five chapters termed bāb, with further subdivisions. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 245r): completed by Sunday, 19 Shavvāl 101[0]/12 April 1602, in the reign of <persName key="viaf_3264079" role="oth">Emperor Akbar I</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Crude illuminated headpiece or sarlawḥ at beginning (f. 1v). 
</p>
                        <p>Neat nastaʿlīq-i khafī alongside s̲uls̲ tending to bihārī. </p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins by multiple hands, including bihārī. 
</p>
                        <p>Persian foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios detached. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f2580">Muḥammad Mujīr Mujībah Adīb</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f2580">محمّد مجير مجيبه اديب</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
